\h Nehemyah
\toc1 Nehemyah
\toc2 Nehemyah
\toc3 Neh.
\mt1 Nehemyah
\mt2 (Nehemiah)
\mt3 rebuilds Yerushalem's walls
\is1 Introduction
\ip \bk Nehemyah\bk* (Nehemiah) was a servant of Persian King Artahshashta (Artaxerxes) in the city of Susa. While he was there, he heard an account from some Israelis who'd been allowed to return back to Yerushalem (Jerusalem) about how hard it was to live there. Yahweh's temple had been rebuilt, however the city wall hadn't been fixed yet, so their enemies who surrounded them were easily able to ambush and attack them.
\ip Because of that, Nehemyah requested permission from the king to go personally to Yerushalem to supervise the rebuilding of the city walls.
\ip In this document we read how God helped Nehemyah of organise the rebuild of the city wall in the middle of the opposition from their enemies around them.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 Nehemyah's returning back to Yerushalem \ior 1:1вҖ“2:20\ior*
\io1 The rebuilding of Yerushalem's city wall \ior 3:1вҖ“7:73\ior*
\io1 The reading of the law and the renewal of their agreement \ior 8:1вҖ“10:39\ior*
\io1 Nehemyah's other achievements \ior 11:1вҖ“13:31\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\rem /s1 Nehemiah's Prayer; Nehemiah's mission; Nehemiah Prays for His People
\p
\v 1 The account by Hakalyah's son NehemyahВҰ221830 \add (NehemiahВҰ221830)\add*.
\s1 Nehemyah's prayer for Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Nehemiah's Concern for Jerusalem
\p In the monthВҰ221835 of KislevВҰ221837 during the twentiethВҰ221840 yearВҰ221839 \add of the reign of King Artahshashta (Artaxerxes) over the Persian Empire\add*, I was inВҰ221835 the capital city of ShushanВҰ221843 \add (SusaВҰ221843)\add*.
\v 2 HananiВҰ221847, one of my brothersВҰ221849, cameВҰ221846 \add вүҲwith some other\add* menВҰ221851 from YehudahВҰ221852, and I askedВҰ221853 them about the Jews who'd escapedВҰ221857 \add вүҲand managed to avoid being exiled\add*, and about YerushalemВҰ221866,
\v 3 and he told me, вҖңThe ones left behind in the provincesВҰ221878 and who \add вүҲavoided\add* the captivityВҰ221876, are in \add вүҲa bad way and feeling depressed\add*. The wallВҰ221882 around YerushalemВҰ221883 was torn down, and its gatesВҰ221885 were burntВҰ221886.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 WhenВҰ221889 I heardВҰ221890 \add вүҲall that\add*, I satВҰ221896 down and I \add вүҲwas upset for daysВҰ221899\add*. I fasted and cried and prayedВҰ221902 to the godВҰ221904 of the heavensВҰ221905,
\v 5 and I saidВҰ221907, вҖңOh YahwehВҰ221909, God of the heavensВҰ221911, the greatВҰ221913 and awesomeВҰ221914 God, who keepsВҰ221915 \add &his\add* agreement and \add вүҲis determinedly loyalВҰ221917\add* to those who loveВҰ221918 himВҰ221918 and \add вүҲobey his instructions\add*:
\v 6 Please listenВҰ221930 \add вүҲcarefully\add* to your servant's prayerВҰ221933 that I'm \add вүҲpresenting to you\add* today, day and nightВҰ221941, on account of your servants the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*. \add вүҲOn behalf of all Israelis\add*, I'm confessingВҰ221947 that we've sinned against youвҖ”\add вүҲboth my generation and previous generations\add*.
\v 7 We've actedВҰ221964 extremely corruptlyвҖ”\add вүҲdisobeying\add* you by not \add вүҲobeying your\add* commandsВҰ221971, statutesВҰ221974, and judgementsВҰ221977 thatВҰ221978 you \add вүҲinstructedВҰ221979 through\add* your servantВҰ221983 MoshehВҰ221982.
\v 8 Please remember \add вүҲthat you toldВҰ221992\add* your servantВҰ221996 MoshehВҰ221995 \add вүҲthat if we act unfaithfullyВҰ221999, you yourself would scatterВҰ222001 us\add* amongВҰ222003 the nations,\x + \xo 1:8: \xt Lev 26:33.\x*
\v 9 \add вүҲbutВҰ222005 if we'd returnВҰ222005 to you and obey your instructions, thenВҰ222005 even if we had been banishedВҰ222014 to the ends of the earth, you'd gatherВҰ222018 us back up and bringВҰ222019 us back to the placeВҰ222023 whereВҰ222024 you've established your nameВҰ222029 and reputationВҰ222029\add*.\x + \xo 1:9: \xt Deu 30:1-5.\x*
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add вүҲWe're your\add* servantsВҰ222033 andВҰ222032 your peopleВҰ222034 that youВҰ222036 \add вүҲrescued from slavery\add* withВҰ222037 your \add вүҲincredible powerВҰ222037\add*.
\v 11 Oh, my masterВҰ222043, please \add вүҲlisten carefully\add* to your servant's prayer, and to the prayer of your \add other\add* servants who delightВҰ222057 to \add вүҲhonour\add* your nameВҰ222061. PleaseВҰ222042 cause your servant to succeedВҰ222062 today, and give \add вүҲme favour in the king's eyes\add*.вҖқ
\p Now as for me, I was the king's cupbearer.
\c 2
\s1 Nehemyah gets sent to Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Nehemiah Goes to Jerusalem; Nehemiah Sent to Judah; Artaxerxes Sends Nehemiah to Jerusalem
\p
\v 1 In the \add вүҲspring\add* of the twentiethВҰ222083 year of KingВҰ222085 Artahshashta's reign, I \add вүҲwas serving\add* wine to the king. \add вүҲI'd never looked sad beforeВҰ222087 inВҰ222080 hisВҰ222087 presenceВҰ222098\add*,
\v 2 andВҰ222100 the kingВҰ222102 \add вүҲasked\add* me, вҖңWhy \add вүҲdo you look unhappy\add*? \add вүҲI know that\add* you'reВҰ222108 not sickВҰ222109 \add вүҲso something must be upsetting you\add*.вҖқ
\p I was very scared
\v 3 and I \add вүҲanswered\add* the king, вҖңMay the king live foreverВҰ222124. \add вүҲI can'tВҰ222127 help butВҰ222121 look unhappy when the cityВҰ222132 containing my ancestors' graves has had its gatesВҰ222138 burnt down and it's now abandoned\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 2:3: \xt 2Ki 25:8-10; 2Ch 36:19; Jer 52:12-14.\x*
\v 4 вҖң\add вүҲSo what would youВҰ222151 like to happen\add*?вҖқ the kingВҰ222145 \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p Then I prayedВҰ222153 to the godВҰ222156 of heavenВҰ222157
\v 5 and \add вүҲanswered\add* the king, вҖңIf \add вүҲI have your favour, and if it seems\add* good to the king, \add maybe\add* you'd send me to YehudahВҰ222176вҖ”to the cityВҰ222179 of my ancestors' graves \add вүҲso I could\add* rebuildВҰ222182 it.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ222184 the king said to me, with the queenВҰ222187 sittingВҰ222189 besideВҰ222190 him, вҖң\add вүҲHow long would\add* your journeyВҰ222195 be? And when would you returnВҰ222197?вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ222184 I gave him a date andВҰ222184 he seemed happy with it, because he released me to go\add*.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲThenВҰ222207 I made another request\add*, вҖңIf it \add вүҲpleases\add* the king, let lettersВҰ222215 be given to me for the governorsВҰ222221 of \add вүҲthe provinces across the Euphrates riverВҰ222223 to ask them to help me in my travel towards\add* YehudahВҰ222232.
\v 8 \add Also\add* a letterВҰ222234 to AsafВҰ222237, the keeper of the king's forestВҰ222239, so he'll give me timber for the beamsВҰ222247 of the gatesВҰ222250 of the fortressВҰ222251 \add вүҲnear the temple\add*, and for the cityВҰ222256 wall, and for the house \add вүҲthatВҰ222240 I'llВҰ222260 live in\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ222234 the king \add вүҲgrantedВҰ222262 those requests, thanks to God's help on what I was doing\add*.
\rem /s1 The city walls rebuilt
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ222272 I wentВҰ222272 to the governorsВҰ222275 of \add вүҲthe provinces across the Euphrates\add*, and I gave them the king's lettersВҰ222282. The king had sent army officers and horsemenВҰ222289 with me.
\v 10 When SanvallatВҰ222293 the HoroniteВҰ222294 and the servantВҰ222296 ToviyyahВҰ222295 the AmmoniteВҰ222297 heard \add >my plans\add*, \add вүҲthey were very angry that someoneВҰ222305 would comeВҰ222304 to help the IsraelisВҰ222309\add*.
\rem /s1 Nehemiah Inspects Jerusalem's Wall; Nehemiah Inspects Jerusalem's Walls; Nehemiah's Inspection of the Walls
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ222311\add* IВҰ222315 \add вүҲgot\add* to YerushalemВҰ222314 andВҰ222315 was thereВҰ222317 for threeВҰ222319 daysВҰ222318,
\v 12 \add вүҲOne nightВҰ222323, I got up andВҰ222321 took a few menВҰ222325 withВҰ222351 me, without having told anyone what I felt that my godВҰ222334 had been telling me\add* to do for YerushalemВҰ222340. \add вүҲWe only had the one horse\add* that I was ridingВҰ222350,
\v 13 and we wentВҰ222353 out \add вүҲinВҰ222354 the dark\add* through the Valley Gate and past the Dragon Well to the Dung Gate. I was \add вүҲcarefully inspecting\add* the \add *city\add* wallsВҰ222369вҖ”\add вүҲnoting\add* where theyВҰ222376 were broken down and whichВҰ222371 gatesВҰ222375 had been burnt out.
\v 14 ThenВҰ222379 I crossed to the Fountain Gate andВҰ222379 the Royal Pool, butВҰ222379 thereВҰ222388 was nowhere that we could get my mountВҰ222391 throughВҰ222392 \add the rubble\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ222395\add* I wentВҰ222403 up the creek bed \add вүҲinВҰ222397 the dark, carefully inspecting\add* the wallВҰ222401, before turning back andВҰ222395 returningВҰ222406 \add quietly\add* through the Valley Gate.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲNone of the city officials\add* knew whereВҰ222411 I'd gone or what I was doingВҰ222415, andВҰ222408 \add up untilВҰ222423 this point\add* I hadn't yet told \add >my plans\add* to the Jewish \add leaders\add* or the priestsВҰ222417 or noblesВҰ222418 or city officials, or \add вүҲhired any workers\add*.
\rem /s1 Decision to Restore the Walls
\v 17 \add вүҲSo now\add* I told them, вҖңYou call all see the \add вүҲdesperate situation\add* thatВҰ222434 we're in: YerushalemВҰ222438 is \add вүҲin ruins\add* and itsВҰ222440 gatesВҰ222440 have been burntВҰ222441 out. \add вүҲSo now,\add* let's rebuildВҰ222444 the \add *city\add* wallВҰ222447 and thenВҰ222429 we'll no longer be \add вүҲmocked by others\add*.вҖқ
\v 18 I told them how GodВҰ222460 \add вүҲhad helped\add* me \add so far\add* and what the kingВҰ222469 had \add вүҲgiven me permission to do\add*.
\p вҖң\add Well,\add* \add вүҲlet's get started on the rebuildingВҰ222476\add*,вҖқ theyВҰ222474 saidВҰ222474, and \add вүҲgot ready to work together\add*.
\v 19 \add вүҲButВҰ222482 then\add* Sanvallat the HoroniteВҰ222484, and the AmmoniteВҰ222488 servantВҰ222487 Toviyyah, and GeshemВҰ222489 the ArabianВҰ222490 heard, and theyВҰ222495 mockedВҰ222491 and despisedВҰ222493 us, saying, вҖңWhat \add вүҲare you guys all up to\add*? Are you all rebellingВҰ222506 againstВҰ222503 the kingВҰ222504?вҖқ
\p
\v 20 I \add вүҲanswered them by explaining\add*, вҖңThe GodВҰ222513 of the heavensВҰ222514 will \add вүҲhelp\add* us to succeedВҰ222516, and we ourselves, his servantsВҰ222519, will \add вүҲdo the rebuildingВҰ222521 work\add*, butВҰ222508 youВҰ222522 all will have \add вүҲno part in it, and no rightsВҰ222526\add* in YerushalemВҰ222528.вҖқ
\c 3
\s1 Rebuilding Yerushalem's wall
\rem /s1 Rebuilding the Wall of Jerusalem; Organization of the Work; Builders of the Wall
\p
\v 1 The highВҰ222533 priest Elyashiv \add вүҲworked together\add* with his brothersВҰ222534 the priestsВҰ222535, and they rebuiltВҰ222536 the Sheep Gate. They themselves dedicated it and installed the doorsВҰ222544 on it. \add вүҲIn addition,\add* they dedicated \add @the section of the wall\add* as far as the Tower of the HundredВҰ222548 and \add вүҲbeyond that to\add* the Tower of HananelВҰ222552.
\p
\v 2 The menВҰ222559 from YerichoВҰ222560 rebuilt \add вүҲthe section beside them\add*, and Imri'sВҰ222569 son Zakkur rebuilt \add вүҲthe next section again\add*.
\v 3 Hassena'ah's son rebuiltВҰ222575 the Fish GateвҖ”laying the beamsВҰ222579 then installing the doorsВҰ222581 with their boltsВҰ222582 and bars.
\p
\v 4 Uriyyah's son MeremotВҰ222590 (the son of Hakkoz'sВҰ222596 son Uriyyah) \add вүҲrebuilt a section, as did\add* MeshullamВҰ222602 (son of Mesheyzav's son BerekyahВҰ222605) and Ba'ana's son TsadokВҰ222614.
\v 5 The TekoitesВҰ222624 \add вүҲworked next to them\add*, butВҰ222620 theirВҰ222622 \add вүҲleaders wouldn't actually help withВҰ222630 the workВҰ222630\add*.
\p
\v 6 Paseah'sВҰ222641 son Yoyada and Besodeyah'sВҰ222645 son MeshullamВҰ222642 rebuilt the YeshanahВҰ222636 GateвҖ”laying the beamsВҰ222647 then installing the doorsВҰ222649 with their boltsВҰ222650 and bars.
\v 7 \add вүҲNext to them was\add* MelatyahВҰ222658 the Gibeonite, YadonВҰ222660 the MeronotiteВҰ222661, and menВҰ222662 of GibeonВҰ222663 and Mitspah \add rebuilding the section\add* to the \add вүҲresidence of the governorВҰ222666 of the regions that side of the Euphrates\add*.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲNext again was\add* Harhayah'sВҰ222678 son Uzziyel (one of the goldsmithsВҰ222679), then HananyahВҰ222685 (who was a son of the perfumersВҰ222688) rebuilt as far as the Broad Wall.
\v 9 \add вүҲThen it was\add* Hur'sВҰ222703 son Refayah, the administrator for half of the YerushalemВҰ222707 districtВҰ222706.
\v 10 Harumaf'sВҰ222717 son YedayahВҰ222714 \add вүҲrepaired the section\add* in front of his houseВҰ222719, then Hashavneyah's son Hatthush \add вүҲmade the next repairs\add*.
\p
\v 11 Harim'sВҰ222736 son Malkiyyah and Pahat-Moav's son Hashshuv repairedВҰ222732 a section, as well as the Tower of Ovens.
\v 12 \add вүҲNext to them was\add* Hallohesh'sВҰ222754 son ShallumВҰ222751, the administrator for \add another\add* half of the YerushalemВҰ222758 districtВҰ222757, helped by his daughtersВҰ222760.
\p
\v 13 HanunВҰ222767 and the inhabitantsВҰ222768 of ZanoahВҰ222769 rebuiltВҰ222771 the Valley GateвҖ”installing the doorsВҰ222773 withВҰ222778 their boltsВҰ222774 and bars, as well as repairingВҰ222766 500m of wallВҰ222778 along to the Dung Gate.
\v 14 Rekav's son Malkiyyah, the administrator for the Beyt-Hakkarem districtВҰ222793, rebuiltВҰ222798 the Dung GateвҖ”installing the doorsВҰ222800 with their boltsВҰ222801 andВҰ222783 bars.
\p
\v 15 Kol-Hozeh'sВҰ222814 son ShallunВҰ222809, the administrator for the Mitspah districtВҰ222816, rebuiltВҰ222819 the Fountain GateвҖ”he built and coveredВҰ222820 it, installing the doorsВҰ222823 with their boltsВҰ222824 and bars, and \add repairedВҰ222808\add* the wallВҰ222827 of the ShelahВҰ222829 \add (Siloam)\add* Pool from the king's gardenВҰ222830 as far as the stairs thatВҰ222836 come down from the City of DavidВҰ222838.
\v 16 \add вүҲNext to\add* himВҰ222841 was Azbuk'sВҰ222846 son NehemyahВҰ222843, the administrator for half of the Beyt-TsurВҰ222852 districtВҰ222849
\rem /s1 Levites Who Worked on the Wall
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲNext to\add* himВҰ222867 were some LevitesВҰ222869: Bani'sВҰ222873 son RehumВҰ222870, then Hashavyah (the administrator for half of the KeilahВҰ222884 district) did his district,
\v 18 \add вүҲthen\add* Henadad'sВҰ222894 son BavvaiВҰ222891 the administrator for \add the other\add* half of the KeilahВҰ222898 districtВҰ222897.
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲThen there was\add* Yeshu'a's son Etser (the administrator of Mitspah) repairedВҰ222901 a section opposite the steps up to the armouryВҰ222915 where the wall turned at an angleВҰ222916.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲThen\add* Tsakkay's son Baruk enthusiastically repairedВҰ222921 another section from that angleВҰ222931 to the entranceВҰ222934 to the houseВҰ222935 of the highВҰ222938 priestВҰ222937 Elyashiv.
\v 21 \add вүҲNext to him was\add* MeremotВҰ222943 (son of Hakots' son Uriyyah) who repairedВҰ222942 another section from the doorway of Elyashiv's house to the end of \add *it\add*.
\rem /s1 Priests Who Worked on the Wall
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲNext to them\add*, some priestsВҰ222964 from the surroundingВҰ222966 area \add вүҲmade repairsВҰ222963\add*.
\p
\v 23 AfterВҰ222968 them BenyaminВҰ222970 and Hashshuv repaired a section \add вүҲin front of\add* theirВҰ222973 house, then AzaryahВҰ222977 (son of Ananyah'sВҰ222983 son Ma'aseyah) repaired besideВҰ222984 his house,
\v 24 Henadad'sВҰ222993 son BinnuiВҰ222990 repairedВҰ222989 another section from Azaryah'sВҰ222997 houseВҰ222996 to the cornerВҰ223003,
\v 25 Uzai'sВҰ223008 son Palal did oppositeВҰ223009 the corner and the towerВҰ223011 above the \add вүҲpalace\add* by the guards' courtyardВҰ223017, \add and\add* then Parosh'sВҰ223023 son PedayahВҰ223020.
\rem /s1 Other Builders
\p
\v 26 The templeВҰ223026 servantsВҰ223026 who lived inВҰ223029 OfelВҰ223029 \add repaired\add* as far as \add вүҲthe easternВҰ223034 side\add* of the Water Gate and its towerВҰ223035.
\v 27 After \add #them\add*, the men from TekoaВҰ223041 repairedВҰ223040 another section from oppositeВҰ223044 thatВҰ223047 tall towerВҰ223045 to the OfelВҰ223050 wallВҰ223049.
\p
\v 28 The priestsВҰ223057 repaired \add вүҲthe section past\add* the Horse GateвҖ”each of them repairing the section in frontВҰ223059 of his own houseВҰ223060.
\v 29 \add вүҲNext to them\add*, Immer'sВҰ223068 son TsadokВҰ223065 repaired opposite his houseВҰ223070, then Shecanyah'sВҰ223077 son ShemayahВҰ223074 the gatekeeper at the Eastern Gate \add вүҲrepaired\add* \add the next section\add*.
\p
\v 30 After him was Shelemyah'sВҰ223089 son HananyahВҰ223086 with Zalaf'sВҰ223093 sixthВҰ223094 son HanunВҰ223090 working on a secondВҰ223096 section, then Berekyah'sВҰ223103 sib MeshullamВҰ223100 repairing a section in front of his quartersВҰ223105.
\v 31 \add вүҲNext was\add* the goldsmiths' son Malkiyyah who repairedВҰ223110 as far as the houseВҰ223117 of the templeВҰ223118 servantsВҰ223118 and the merchantsВҰ223119, opposite the Inspection Gate, and up to the upper room in the cornerВҰ223125,
\v 32 and the other goldsmithsВҰ223133 and some merchantsВҰ223134 repairedВҰ223132 \add the last section of the wall\add* from the upper room in the cornerВҰ223129 to the Sheep Gate.
\c 4
\s1 The opposition to Nehemyah
\rem /s1 Nehemiah Overcomes Opposition to His Work; Opposition to the Rebuilding; Hostile Plots Thwarted; Enemies Oppose the Rebuilding
\p
\v 1 When SanballatВҰ223259 heardВҰ223258 that we were rebuilding the wall, he got really angry. He mocked the Jews
\v 2 and he spoke before \add вүҲinВҰ223285 front\add* of his brothers and the army of Shomron \add (Samaria)\add*, вҖңWhat are those feeble Jews doing? \add вүҲDo they think they'll be able to rebuild that place\add* themselves? Will they sacrifice? Will they \add вүҲget finished one\add* day? Will they form the stones \add вүҲback togetherВҰ223282\add* from piles of dust, when they've been \add вүҲweakened by the heat of the fires\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 3 Toviyyah the Ammonite was \add вүҲstanding beside him and confirmed\add*, вҖңYes, even if a fox \add вүҲwalked over\add* that stone wall that they're building, it would make \add вүҲit fall down\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add I prayed,\add* вҖңOur god, \add вүҲlisten to how we're mocked\add* and cause their \add вүҲwords\add* to return onВҰ223314 their \add own\add* heads and \add вүҲsend them away as captives to become the plunder for another country\add*.
\v 5 Don't just cover over their evil, and don'tВҰ223319 \add вүҲjust ignore their sin\add*, because they've \add repeatedly\add* \add вүҲmade the workers get angry\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ223341 we kept on at building\add* the wall, and \add eventually\add* all the \add segments of\add* wall were joined up together \add вүҲup to about half its full height\add*, and \add so\add* the people \add вүҲwere encouraged to keep persevering\add*.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲNow\add* when Sanballat, and Toviyyah, and the Arabians, and the Ammonites, and the Ashdodites heard that the Yerushalem walls \add вүҲwere getting repaired\add* and the breaks were beginning to be closed up, it \add вүҲmade them extremely angry\add*
\v 8 and they all got together to come to \add вүҲattack\add* Yerushalem and \add вүҲto throw us into confusion\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ223421\add* weВҰ223427 prayed to ourВҰ223414 god, \add вүҲas well as setting up a 24-hour guard to watch out for\add* them.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲPeople around YehudahВҰ223458\add* said, вҖңThe \add вүҲworkers are running out of\add* strength and there's \add вүҲa lot of\add* rubble \add still to be moved\add*. \add вүҲMaybe we're not up to building this\add* wall.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 Then \add вүҲthoseВҰ223463 against us\add* said, вҖң\add вүҲWe'll rush inВҰ223462 among them and kill some of them before they even see us or know that we're coming\add*, then \add вүҲthat will bring the workВҰ223469 to an end\add*.вҖқ
\v 12 \add вүҲAfter\add* that, whenever the Jews living close to them came, theyВҰ223482 \add вүҲrepeatedly warned us\add*, вҖң\add вүҲThey're going to attack us from all directions\add*.вҖқ
\v 13 \add вүҲSo\add* I stationed \add guards\add* behind the lowest places along the wallВҰ223506 \add вүҲand where there were still gaps\add*. I \add also\add* \add вүҲmade sure that the families stood guard\add* with their swords, spears, and bows.
\p
\v 14 I looked then I \add вүҲgot organised\add* and told the nobles and the prefects, and the rest of the people, вҖңDon't be afraid of their \add вүҲthreats\add*. Remember my \add вүҲpowerful\add* and fearsome master, and fightВҰ223523 for your brothers, your sons and your daughters, your wives, and your houses.вҖқ
\v 15 \add вүҲAfter all that\add*, when our enemies \add вүҲrealised that we were aware of their intentions and that God had frustrated their surprise attack plan\add*, \add вүҲwe all returned to our workВҰ223529 onВҰ223529\add* the wall.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲSo from that dayВҰ223555 onwards\add*, half of my young men would \add вүҲworkВҰ223556 onВҰ223541 the rebuilding, while the other half stood guardВҰ223554 withВҰ223541\add* spears, shields, and breastplates, and the officials \add вүҲencouraged them all from behind\add*.
\v 17 \add BothВҰ223560\add* those who were \add вүҲplacing the stones on\add* the wall and those who were carrying the heavy loads \add to them\add*, \add always\add* \add вүҲhad their weaponsВҰ223573 with them\add* \add in case of an attack\add*.
\v 18 The builders \add вүҲhad their swords strapped to their sides as they worked\add*, and \add вүҲthe man who would sound the trumpet stayed with\add* me.
\v 19 Then I told the nobles and prefects, and the rest of the people, вҖң\add вүҲThis job is so large and extensive that we're all separated from each other when we work on\add* the wall,
\v 20 \add so\add* whenever you all hear the trumpet blast, join us at that place. Our god will fight for us.вҖқ
\v 21 \add вүҲSo\add* we \add вүҲcontinued the work with\add* half of them keeping their hands on their spears from the \add вүҲbeginning of the day\add* until the stars came out \add at night\add*.
\p
\v 22 Also at that time, I told the people, вҖң\add вүҲEvery worker including servants should spend the night inside the city, so they double as workers during the day and guards at\add* night.вҖқ
\v 23 \add During that period of construction,\add* none of us, not even our servants, \add вүҲstayed undressed\add* or \add вүҲseparated from our weapons, even when washing\add*.
\c 5
\s1 The resolution of Nehemyah of problem
\rem /s1 Oppression of the Poor; Nehemiah Defends the Oppressed; Nehemiah Deals with Oppression; Nehemiah's social reforms; Nehemiah Helps the Poor
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ223585\add* \add around then,\add* there was a \add вүҲwidespread complaint from\add* the peopleВҰ223579 and their wivesВҰ223580 againstВҰ223582 \add вүҲwhat their fellow Jews were doing\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲSome of them complained\add*, вҖң\add вүҲThere's a lot of us when we include\add* our sonsВҰ223590 and daughtersВҰ223591. \add вүҲWe need\add* grainВҰ223595 so we can eatВҰ223596 and \add вүҲstay alive\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲOthers\add* said, вҖңWe are mortgagingВҰ223606 our fieldsВҰ223602 and vineyardsВҰ223603, and our housesВҰ223604 so weВҰ223605 can get grainВҰ223608 during this famineВҰ223609.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲYet others\add* said, вҖңWe've borrowedВҰ223614 silver \add to pay the taxВҰ223616\add* on our fieldsВҰ223618 andВҰ223611 our vineyardsВҰ223619 \add вүҲthat goes to the tributeВҰ223616 to be paid to\add* the \add foreign\add* kingВҰ223617.
\v 5 \add вүҲWe're Jews just like our countrymenВҰ223623, butВҰ223621 we're having to commit our children into bondage as slavesВҰ223636вҖ”yes, even\add* our daughters. \add вүҲNow we own nothing at allвҖ”not even\add* our fieldsВҰ223643 andВҰ223621 vineyardsВҰ223644.
\p
\v 6 I got very angry when I heardВҰ223651 theirВҰ223654 \add вүҲcomplaints andВҰ223655 desperation\add*,
\v 7 and \add вүҲI couldn't get itВҰ223659 out of my mindВҰ223660\add*. I \add вүҲprotested\add* to the noblesВҰ223665 and the officialsВҰ223668, вҖңYou guys are \add вүҲcharging interest againstВҰ223682 your own countrymen\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 5:7: \xt Exo 22:25; Lev 25:35-37; Deu 23:19-20.\x*
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ223659 I calledВҰ223681 for a gathering of all the people to deal withВҰ223675\add* them,
\v 8 and I told them, вҖңOur brothers, the Jews, were sold to \add other\add* countriesВҰ223695 \add as slaves\add* \add вүҲand we've done all we can to bring them back here\add*. ButВҰ223686 now even you yourselves are buying and selling your own countrymen \add to make a profit\add*.вҖқ They \add вүҲcouldn't argue against that, so they were just\add* silentВҰ223708.
\p
\v 9 вҖңIt's not goodВҰ223720 what you're doingВҰ223725,вҖқ I \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ223714\add*. вҖңShouldn't you all \add вүҲrespect and obey\add* our godВҰ223728, because \add вүҲotherwise we'll be despised by the other\add* nationsВҰ223731, our enemiesВҰ223732.
\v 10 IВҰ223736 myself have lent them moneyВҰ223741 and grainВҰ223742, as have my brothersВҰ223737 and my young men, \add butВҰ223734\add* pleaseВҰ223745 let's forgo charging interestВҰ223748.
\v 11 Please, even today, return their fieldsВҰ223755 to them, and their vineyardsВҰ223756 and oliveВҰ223757 orchards, their housesВҰ223758, and \add вүҲthe interest onВҰ223767\add* the moneyВҰ223760 and the grainВҰ223761, the new wine, and the oilВҰ223763 thatВҰ223764 youВҰ223765 are charging against them.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖң\add вүҲOkay, we'll do what you'reВҰ223777 asking\add*,вҖқ they \add вүҲrespondedВҰ223769\add*. вҖңWe'll returnВҰ223770 \add >their property\add* and we \add вүҲwon'tВҰ223772 impose any more charges on\add* them.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ223769\add* I calledВҰ223779 the priestsВҰ223782 \add вүҲto witness those nobles and officials making an oath to do what they'd saidВҰ223769 they would do\add*.
\v 13 Also I shookВҰ223791 \add вүҲthe foldsВҰ223790 of my robeВҰ223790\add* and told \add >them\add*, вҖңMay God shake you all out of his houseВҰ223809 like that, and \add вүЎshake\add* \add вүҲevery man's business if he doesn't do what he just promisedВҰ223826\add*вҖ”may he be shakenВҰ223813 out like that and \add вүҲlose everything\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Generosity of Nehemiah; Nehemiah's Unselfishness
\s1 Nehemyah's generosity
\p
\v 14 Also, from the dayВҰ223830 that I was appointedВҰ223834 to be theirВҰ223837 governor in the YehudahВҰ223839 regionВҰ223838 (for the twelve yearsВҰ223848 from \add the Persian\add* KingВҰ223847 Artahshashta's 20th year until his 32nd year), I myself didn'tВҰ223855 \add вүҲaccept the governor's food allowance\add*, nor did my \add вүҲrelatives\add*.
\v 15 The governorsВҰ223858 who preceded me had been very \add вүҲhard\add* onВҰ223869 the peopleвҖ”\add вүҲdemanding\add* bread and wine and fortyВҰ223875 silverВҰ223872 coins. Even theirВҰ223877 servantsВҰ223877 \add вүҲoppressed\add* the people. \add In contrast,\add* I didn'tВҰ223883 do that \add вүҲdue to desire to honour\add* GodВҰ223889.
\v 16 Also I \add вүҲremained focussed onВҰ223892 rebuilding the\add* wallВҰ223893, and weВҰ223898 \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ223897 invest inВҰ223892 a farm property\add*, and all my servantsВҰ223901 \add вүҲalso contributed\add* to the work.
\v 17 \add вүҲI regularly fed a hundredВҰ223910 and fiftyВҰ223911 Jewish leaders and city officialsВҰ223909, as well as visitors from other countriesВҰ223917\add* aroundВҰ223920 us,
\v 18 \add вүҲso in one dayВҰ223928 we needed\add* one bullВҰ223930, sixВҰ223933 choice sheepВҰ223932, \add вүҲandВҰ223925 various kinds of poultryВҰ223936\add*, as well as various types of wines every tenВҰ223941 daysВҰ223942. \add вүҲIВҰ223953 didn'tВҰ223952 demand any of this from the peopleВҰ223960 because it would have been a heavyВҰ223956 burdenВҰ223957 for them\add*.
\mi
\v 19 MyВҰ223966 godВҰ223966, remember me for the goodВҰ223967 that I'veВҰ223971 doneВҰ223971 for these peopleВҰ223974.
\c 6
\s1 The plan of killing Nehemyah
\rem /s1 Continued Opposition to Rebuilding; Intrigues of Enemies Foiled; Plots against Nehemiah; Further Opposition to the Rebuilding
\p
\v 1 Although we didn't yet have any doorsВҰ224002 in the gatesВҰ224006, when SanballatВҰ223981 and Toviyyah and GeshemВҰ223983 the ArabianВҰ223984 and the rest of our enemiesВҰ223986 heardВҰ223980 that we'd finished building the wallВҰ223991 so it didn't have any gaps left in it,
\v 2 SanballatВҰ224009 andВҰ224008 GeshemВҰ224010 \add вүҲinvited\add* me, вҖңWe'dВҰ224016 like to arrange to meet withВҰ224016 you inВҰ224016 one of the villagesВҰ224016 onВҰ224016 the OnoВҰ224018 plainВҰ224017.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ224008\add* theyВҰ224019 were \add вүҲintending to harm\add* me.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ224025\add* I sentВҰ224025 messengersВҰ224027 \add back\add* to them, вҖң\add вүҲThis work is important and extensive, so I can'tВҰ224033 afford to abandon it and have the work stop if I travelled down to you on the plain\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 They \add вүҲtried fourВҰ224048 timesВҰ224049 to get me to go, butВҰ224044 I kept refusing them for those sameВҰ224053 reasons\add*.
\p
\v 5 Then SanballatВҰ224058 sent his servantВҰ224065 to me a fifthВҰ224062 time \add вүҲwith the same request, butВҰ224056 this time in an unsealed, open letterВҰ224066\add*
\v 6 sayingВҰ224075, вҖң\add вүҲThere's rumours flying around inВҰ224071 nearby\add* countriesВҰ224072, and GeshemВҰ224074 \add вүҲconfirms itВҰ224071\add*, that you and the Jews are building the wallВҰ224085 because you'reВҰ224083 all plotting thinking to rebelВҰ224079. Then you'd becomeВҰ224087 their kingВҰ224089, accordingВҰ224090 to \add вүҲwhat we're hearing\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲWe've also heard that\add* you'veВҰ224096 set up вҖҳprophetsВҰ224095вҖҷ to speak out in YerushalemВҰ224099 to say about you, вҖҳThere's a king in YehudahВҰ224102.вҖҷ By now, all of that will have been heard by the \add Persian\add* king. \add вүҲSoВҰ224093\add* now, come andВҰ224093 let's \add вүҲdiscuss this\add* togetherВҰ224111.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 I sentВҰ224114 \add вүҲa message straight back\add*, вҖң\add вүҲNone of what you'reВҰ224122 sayingВҰ224123 is true. It's simply yourВҰ224125 own imagination at work\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 \add We knew that\add* they were just trying to frighten us \add вүҲso that we'd stop the repairs and it would never get finished\add*.
\mi \add My god,\add* strengthenВҰ224143 my hands.
\p
\v 10 \add After that,\add* I entered Shemayah'sВҰ224152 house (the son of Mehetav'el's son DelayahВҰ224155) who was confined \add to his house\add*, andВҰ224148 he said, вҖңLet's set a time to meet in the templeвҖ”we'll shut the temple doorsВҰ224172 because they'll be coming to kill youвҖ”probably in the nightВҰ224177.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ224181 I disagreed\add*, вҖңWould a manВҰ224182 like me run away? \add вүҲBesides that, who's allowed to liveВҰ224193 inside the templeВҰ224192\add*? I won'tВҰ224194 \add вүҲdo that\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲThenВҰ224197 I suddenly realised that GodВҰ224201 hadn't told him to say that, butВҰ224197 rather he was working againstВҰ224206 me because he'd been paid by\add* Toviyyah andВҰ224197 SanballatВҰ224208.
\v 13 \add вүҲThey mustВҰ224220 have hiredВҰ224212 him\add* so that I'd be afraidВҰ224216 and \add вүҲtake that advice\add* and sinВҰ224220. \add вүҲThen theyВҰ224226 could have ruined my reputationВҰ224223 and discredited\add* me.
\mi
\v 14 My godВҰ224230, rememberВҰ224229 what Toviyyah and SanballatВҰ224232 have done, and also the prophetess NoadyahВҰ224236 and the other prophets who've been \add вүҲtrying to scare me\add*.
\s1 The completion of wall
\rem /s1 The Conclusion of the Work; The Builders Complete the Wall; The Completion of the Wall; The Wall Completed
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ224245\add* \add the rebuilding of\add* the wallВҰ224246 was finished onВҰ224247 the 25th of SeptemberВҰ224249 inВҰ224247 \add just\add* fifty-two days,
\v 16 and when our enemiesВҰ224260 heardВҰ224257 \add about it\add*, the surroundingВҰ224266 countriesВҰ224264 were afraid \add вүҲand discouraged\add* because they realisedВҰ224261 thatВҰ224265 our godВҰ224273 \add вүҲmust have helped us\add*.
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲDuring thatВҰ224286 timeВҰ224280\add*, the YehudahВҰ224284 noblesВҰ224283 were \add вүҲsending many\add* letters to Toviyyah, andВҰ224290 \add вүЎletters\add* from Toviyyah were \add also\add* comingВҰ224292 to them,
\v 18 because many \add people\add* in YehudahВҰ224298 \add вүҲhad ties withВҰ224298 him\add* because he was the son-in-law of Arah'sВҰ224309 son ShekanyahВҰ224306, plusВҰ224310 his son YehohananВҰ224310 had \add вүҲmarried\add* Berekyah'sВҰ224319 daughterВҰ224315 MeshullamВҰ224317.
\v 19 \add @Those nobles\add* kept tellingВҰ224324 me \add вүҲabout the goodВҰ224322 things heВҰ224331 was doing\add*, and they reported my wordsВҰ224326 \add back\add* to him. ToviyyahВҰ224332 \add also\add* sentВҰ224331 lettersВҰ224330 to \add try to\add* frighten me.
\c 7
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOnceВҰ224339\add* the wallВҰ224338 had been rebuiltВҰ224337 and the doorsВҰ224340 \add вүҲhung\add* in the gates, the gatekeepersВҰ224342 and the singersВҰ224343 and the LevitesВҰ224344 had been appointedВҰ224341.
\v 2 I put my brotherВҰ224350 HananiВҰ224349 and the fortress commanderВҰ224354 Hananyah in charge over YerushalemВҰ224358. (Hananyah was a faithfulВҰ224363 manВҰ224362 and \add вүҲrespected\add* God more than many \add others do\add*.)
\v 3 I told them, вҖңDon't open Yerushalem'sВҰ224376 gatesВҰ224375 untilВҰ224377 \add вүҲbroad daylight\add*, and thenВҰ224370 shut and bar them again while \add вүҲthe guardsВҰ224383 are still on full alert\add*. And \add вүҲassign neighbourhood watch groups among the inhabitantsВҰ224389 to keep an eye on theirВҰ224395 own areas\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The list of returned exiles
\rem /s1 The List of Those Who Returned from Exile; The List of the Exiles Who Returned; Nehemiah Registers the People
\r (Ezra 2:1-70)
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲNow\add* Yerushalem \add вүҲcovered a largeВҰ224400 area butВҰ224397 not many peopleВҰ224401 had returned to live there yet, andВҰ224397 the housesВҰ224405 hadn't yet been rebuiltВҰ224406\add*.
\rem /s1 Lists of the Returned Exiles
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ224408\add* GodВҰ224409 \add вүҲgaveВҰ224408 me the idea of\add* gathering the \add вүҲleaders andВҰ224408 the peopleВҰ224422 grouped by their ancestors\add*. I found the \add вүҲregister of thoseВҰ224427 who'd returned\add* \add from exile to Yerushalem\add*, withВҰ224428 this writtenВҰ224430 inВҰ224428 it:
\p
\v 6 вҖңThese are the descendants of \add вүҲthe people exiledВҰ224440 by the Babylonian KingВҰ224444 Nevukadnetstsar, who returned to YehudahВҰ224448 and to YerushalemВҰ224447вҖ”each family returning to their own ancestral townВҰ224450\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲTheir leaders were\add* Zerubavel, YeshuaВҰ224456, NehemyahВҰ224457, AzaryahВҰ224458, RaamyahВҰ224459, NahamaniВҰ224460, Mareddekai, BilshanВҰ224462, MisperetВҰ224463, BigvaiВҰ224464, NehumВҰ224465, and BaanahВҰ224466.
