\v 59 \add and\add* the descendants of Shefatyah, HattilВҰ224931, Pokeret-Hazzeba'im, and AmonВҰ224936.
\m
\v 60 AltogetherВҰ224943, there were 392 descendants of the \add templeВҰ224940\add* workers and \add conscripted\add* labourers.
\p
\v 61 \add вүҲThere were also some\add* \add who returned\add* from Tel-Melah, Tel-HarshaВҰ224955, Keruv, AddonВҰ224957, and ImmerВҰ224958, \add вүҲeven though they couldn't prove who their ancestorsВҰ224964 were, or even that they were descendantsВҰ224965 of Israelis\add*:
\p
\v 62 There were \add also\add* 642 descendants of DelayahВҰ224972, Toviyyah, and NekodaВҰ224977,
\v 63 plusВҰ224984 some priestsВҰ224986:
\li1 the descendants of Havayah, Hakots, and Barzillai. (Barzillai had married a descendant of a man named Barzillai from Gilead, and had takenВҰ224994 his wife's family nameВҰ225002.)
\m
\v 64 They had search the genealogicalВҰ225007 records for theirВҰ225006 family histories, butВҰ225008 didn'tВҰ225008 find them, \add вүҲso theyВҰ225005 were ineligible to serve as priestsВҰ225013\add*.
\v 65 The governorВҰ225016 \add вүҲhad disallowed them from eating the priests' food\add* untilВҰ225024 a \add recognised\add* priest \add вүҲcould consult\add* the Urim andВҰ225028 ThummimВҰ225028.\x + \xo 7:65: \xt Exo 28:30; Deu 33:8.\x*
\m
\v 66 \add вүҲAltogether\add*, 42,360 people \add returned to Yehudah\add*,
\v 67 \add вүҲnot counting\add* \add theirВҰ225043\add* 7,337 male and female servantsВҰ225043, and 245 male and female singersВҰ225053.
\v 68 \add вүҲThey had\add* 736 horses, 245 mules,
\v 69 435 camels, and 6,720 donkeys.
\v 70 \add вүҲSome of the leaders of the ancestral clans\add* gaveВҰ225097 to the workВҰ225099. The governor donated 8kg of goldВҰ225100, 50 bowls, and 530 robes for the priests,
\v 71 and some of the leaders donated 150kg of goldВҰ225114 and 1,500kg of silverВҰ225118.
\v 72 The rest of the peopleВҰ225135 donated 150kg of gold, 1,300kg of silver, and 67 robes for the priestsВҰ225129.
\p
\v 73 \add вүҲSo\add* the priests and the Levites, the gatekeepers and the singers, the temple workers and the rest of the Israelis, all \add вүҲsettled\add* in their \add various ancestral\add* cities.\x + \xo 7:73: \xt 1Ch 9:2; Neh 11:3.\x*
\c 8
\s1 Ezra reads God's instructions to the people
\rem /s1 Ezra Reads the Law to the People
\p
\v 1 All the peopleВҰ225151 gatheredВҰ225148 \add вүҲtogether in the plaza near\add* the Water Gate andВҰ225162 \add вүҲasked\add* EzraВҰ225163 the scribeВҰ225164 to bringВҰ225165 the scrollВҰ225168 with \add вүҲYahweh's instructionsВҰ225173 to YisraelВҰ225177 given through\add* MoshehВҰ225170 \add (MosesВҰ225170)\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ225179 it was the beginning of October when\add* EzraВҰ225180 the priestВҰ225181 broughtВҰ225179 the \add вүҲscroll\add* to the gathering of men and women and everyoneВҰ225195 who wanted to understandВҰ225192 it,
\v 3 and he \add вүҲread it aloud in the plaza near\add* the Water GateвҖ”reading from dawn untilВҰ225213 the middleВҰ225215 of the dayВҰ225216 in frontВҰ225202 of thoseВҰ225220 men and womenВҰ225219 and \add вүҲinterested peopleВҰ225224, who all listened intently\add*.
\p
\v 4 EzraВҰ225231 the scribeВҰ225232 stood on a raised wooden platformВҰ225235 thatВҰ225238 they had made \add вүҲespecially for this purpose\add*. Standing on his rightВҰ225251 were MattitiahВҰ225243, ShemaВҰ225244, AnayahВҰ225245, Uriyyah, Hilkiyyah, and Ma'aseyah, and on his left stood PedayahВҰ225253, Misha'el, Malkiyyah, HashumВҰ225256, HashbaddanahВҰ225257, ZekaryahВҰ225258, and MeshullamВҰ225259.
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲUp on the platform,\add* EzraВҰ225263 opened the \add вүҲscrollВҰ225264 in front\add* of all the people, and \add вүҲas he did so\add*, all the people stoodВҰ225277 up.
\v 6 EzraВҰ225283 blessedВҰ225282 the greatВҰ225288 God Yahweh and the peopleВҰ225292 \add вүҲraised their arms and responded\add*, вҖңMay it be so.вҖқ ThenВҰ225282 they knelt down and bowedВҰ225298 to Yahweh \add вүҲwithВҰ225296 their faces\add* to the groundВҰ225302.
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ225304 Yeshua, BaniВҰ225305, Shereveyah, YaminВҰ225310, AkkubВҰ225311, ShabtaiВҰ225312, Hodiyyah, Ma'aseyah, KelitaВҰ225316, AzaryahВҰ225317, Yozavad, HananВҰ225319, PelayahВҰ225320, who were all LevitesВҰ225321, \add вүҲexplained what had been read\add* to the people standing there.
\v 8 They read the scrollВҰ225333 containing God's instructions, \add вүҲexplaining how it applied so\add* the people could understandВҰ225339 \add *it\add*.
\p
\v 9 Then NehemyahВҰ225344 the governorВҰ225346 and EzraВҰ225347 the priestВҰ225348 & scribeВҰ225350, and the LevitesВҰ225351 who were \add вүҲexplaining it\add*, said to all the people, вҖңToday is a sacredВҰ225360 dayВҰ225359вҖ”it belongs to your godВҰ225364 Yahweh. Don't mournВҰ225367 or weep.вҖқ \add That was\add* because all the people were weepingВҰ225372 after they heardВҰ225376 \add вүҲYahweh's instructions to them\add*.
\v 10 ThenВҰ225382 \add @Nehemyah\add* told them, вҖңGo \add home and\add* eatВҰ225385 \add вүҲsome special food with sweetВҰ225388 drinkВҰ225387\add*, and \add вүҲshare some with\add* those \add вүҲwho can'tВҰ225399 afford such thingsВҰ225388\add* because today is \add вүҲa sacredВҰ225396 dayВҰ225397 that\add* belongs to ourВҰ225398 masterВҰ225398. And don'tВҰ225399 grieveВҰ225401, because \add вүҲthe happiness from YahwehВҰ225398 will make you all strong\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 The Levites \add вүҲtold the peopleВҰ225413 to quieten down\add*, saying, вҖң\add вүҲDon't grieveВҰ225421 today because it's a sacredВҰ225418 dayВҰ225417. Stay quiet.\add*вҖқ
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ225423\add* all the peopleВҰ225426 went to eat and drinkВҰ225428 and to \add вүҲtake plates of food to others\add*, and to \add вүҲhave a big celebration\add* because they understoodВҰ225435 what \add вүҲhad been read\add* to them.
\s1 The celebration in shelters
\rem /s1 The Festival of Shelters; The Festival of Booths Celebrated
\p
\v 13 The \add вүҲnext\add* dayВҰ225442, \add вүҲall the clan leaders\add*, and the priestsВҰ225450 and LevitesВҰ225451, met withВҰ225442 EzraВҰ225454 the scribeВҰ225455 to \add вүҲstudyВҰ225456 the instructions\add* \add onВҰ225442 the scroll\add*.
\v 14 They \add вүҲdiscovered that it was\add* writtenВҰ225463 in the \add вүҲinstructionsВҰ225466 that YahwehВҰ225467 had given through MoshehВҰ225470\add*, that the IsraelisВҰ225473 should live in \add temporary\add* shelters during the celebration in their seventhВҰ225479 monthВҰ225478 \add (our September-October)\add*.\x + \xo 8:14-15: \xt Lev 23:33-36,39-43; Deu 16:13-15.\x*
\v 15 They should \add вүҲpublicly proclaim\add* in YerushalemВҰ225488 and in all theirВҰ225487 townsВҰ225487 \add вүҲthatВҰ225481 the people should go into the hillsВҰ225491 and bringВҰ225492 back branches from olive or wild olive trees, myrtleВҰ225501 or palmВҰ225503 trees, and/or other\add* leafyВҰ225506 trees to make shelters as it's writtenВҰ225509.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲSo\add* the peopleВҰ225513 wentВҰ225512 out and broughtВҰ225514 \add back branches\add* to make shelters for themselves onВҰ225522 their roofs or in their courtyardsВҰ225522, or in the temple courtyard or in the plazas near the Water Gate and the EfrayimВҰ225531 Gate.
\v 17 ThenВҰ225533 the whole assemblyВҰ225536 \add вүҲof peopleВҰ225555\add* who'd come back from captivityВҰ225540 made shelters and livedВҰ225543 inВҰ225544 them \add for one week\add*. The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ225555\add* hadn't doneВҰ225548 thatВҰ225537 sinceВҰ225549 the \add вүҲtimeВҰ225549 of Yehoshua's leadership\add*, and \add вүҲthey did itВҰ225560 withВҰ225544 a lot of celebration\add*.
\v 18 \add @Ezra\add* read aloud from the scrollВҰ225566 of God'sВҰ225568 instructions each day of the sevenВҰ225582 daysВҰ225583 of celebrationВҰ225579, thenВҰ225565 onВҰ225566 the eighthВҰ225585 day they all gathered together as per the instructions.
\c 9
\s1 The people confess their sins
\rem /s1 The People Confess Their Sins; National Confession; The Israelites Confess Their Sins
\p
\v 1 On the 24th of that monthВҰ225593, the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ225598 dressed inВҰ225590 sackclothВҰ225600, put dust onВҰ225590 their heads, fasted, and gatheredВҰ225595 together\add*.
\v 2 Those of \add вүҲJewish descent stoodВҰ225610 separatelyВҰ225604\add* from the descendants of foreignersВҰ225609, andВҰ225604 they confessedВҰ225611 their \add own\add* sinsВҰ225614, as well as those of their ancestorsВҰ225616.
\v 3 They stoodВҰ225618 and \add вүҲlistened to the scrollВҰ225623 withВҰ225623 Yahweh's instructions being read for three hours\add*, thenВҰ225618 for \add вүҲanother three hours\add* theyВҰ225630 confessedВҰ225630 and bowed down to Yahweh their godВҰ225626.
\v 4 Then YeshuaВҰ225641 went up the Levites' stairs withВҰ225650 Bani, Kadmi'el, Shevanyah, BunniВҰ225645, Shereveyah, \add another\add* Bani, \add and\add* KenaniВҰ225648, and theyВҰ225649 called out loudly to theirВҰ225655 godВҰ225655 YahwehВҰ225654.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ225657 \add вүҲsome\add* LevitesВҰ225658 (YeshuaВҰ225659, Kadmi'el, BaniВҰ225661, Hashavneyah, Shereveyah, Hodiyyah, Shevanyah, and PetahyahВҰ225666) saidВҰ225657, вҖң\add вүҲStand\add* up \add and\add* bless your eternal GodВҰ225672 YahwehВҰ225671: May \add @the peoplesВҰ225679\add* bless your \add вүҲwonderful reputationВҰ225680\add* which is \add вүҲgreater than anything else that we bless or praiseВҰ225688\add*.
\rem /s1 The Prayer of Confession
\v 6 YahwehВҰ225693, you aloneВҰ225694 are \add @God\add*. You yourselfВҰ225694 made the heavens, the \add вүҲgalaxies in\add* the heavens and all theirВҰ225705 \add вүҲstars\add*, the earthВҰ225706 and all that is on it, the seas and all that is in them. You \add вүҲgive life to everything\add*, and \add вүҲall the stars bow down\add* to you.
\p
\v 7 вҖңYou are YahwehВҰ225729, the god who choseВҰ225732 AbramВҰ225733. Then you broughtВҰ225734 him out from UrВҰ225735 inВҰ225733 the \add вүҲChaldean region\add*, then you \add вүҲrenamed him to\add* AbrahamВҰ225739 \add (meaning вҖҳfather of manyвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 8 You \add вүҲdiscovered that he was sincere and faithfulВҰ225745 to you, and made an agreement with him\add*вҖ”to give the CanaaniteВҰ225754, HittiteВҰ225755, AmoriteВҰ225756, PerizziteВҰ225757, YebusiteВҰ225758, and the GirgashiteВҰ225759 \add вүҲregionsВҰ225753\add* to his descendantsВҰ225761, and you have \add вүҲensured that it's all come to be\add* because you're righteousВҰ225767.\x + \xo 9:8: \xt Gen 15:18-21.\x*
\v 9 You \add вүҲnoticedВҰ225770 the suffering\add* of ourВҰ225774 ancestorsВҰ225774 \add enslaved\add* inВҰ225775 EgyptВҰ225775, andВҰ225776 thenВҰ225770 youВҰ225779 heardВҰ225779 theirВҰ225778 cryВҰ225778 \add for help\add* \add вүҲatВҰ225775 the edge of\add* the Red Sea.
\p
\v 10 вҖңYou \add вүҲdisplayed miracles\add* to Far-oh \add (PharaohВҰ225789)\add*, and to all his servantsВҰ225792 and to all the \add вүҲEgyptian\add* peopleВҰ225795, because you knewВҰ225798 that they were acting \add вүҲas if you weren't real\add*, \add вүҲso you got yourselfВҰ225804 a reputationВҰ225805 which you still have to\add* this dayВҰ225806.\x + \xo 9:10: \xt Exo 7:8вҖ“12:32.\x*
\v 11 ThenВҰ225809 you splitВҰ225810 the sea open the sea \add вүҲright in front of their eyes\add*, andВҰ225809 they \add вүҲwalked\add* through the middleВҰ225813 of \add *it\add* onВҰ225813 dry land. \add вүҲAfter that,\add* you \add вүҲdrowned\add* their pursuersВҰ225819 into the \add вүҲdeep sea\add* like a stoneВҰ225824 in \add вүҲa huge lakeВҰ225809\add*.\x + \xo 9:11: a \xt Exo 14:21-29; \xo b \xt Exo 15:4-5.\x*
\v 12 You led them \add вүҲduring the\add* dayВҰ225831 with a pillar of cloudВҰ225829, andВҰ225832 \add вүҲduring the\add* nightВҰ225834 with a pillar of fireВҰ225833 to illuminate the wayВҰ225839 thatВҰ225840 theyВҰ225841 should go.\x + \xo 9:12: \xt Exo 13:21-22.\x*
\p
\v 13 вҖңThenВҰ225845 you cameВҰ225849 down to MtВҰ225846. SinaiВҰ225848 and spokeВҰ225850 with them from the sky, and you gaveВҰ225853 to them \add вүҲprinciples of justice\add* and laws of truthвҖ”goodВҰ225861 statutesВҰ225859 and instructionsВҰ225859.\x + \xo 9:13-14: \xt Exo 19:18вҖ“23:33.\x*
\v 14 You \add вүҲrevealed the concept of a rest day\add* to them, and you \add вүҲgave\add* them rules and instructionsВҰ225873 and laws via yourВҰ225866 servantВҰ225877 MoshehВҰ225876 \add (MosesВҰ225876)\add*.
\p
\v 15 вҖңYou gaveВҰ225881 them breadВҰ225879 from the sky \add вүҲwhen they were hungry\add*, andВҰ225879 you \add вүҲmade\add* waterВҰ225884 \add вүҲcome out of a rockВҰ225885 when they were thirstyВҰ225888\add*, thenВҰ225879 \add eventually\add* you told them to goВҰ225891 \add вүҲahead\add* to possessВҰ225892 the land that you had \add вүҲsaidВҰ225889 that you'd\add* giveВҰ225902 to them.\x + \xo 9:15: a \xt Exo 16:4-15; \xo b \xt Exo 17:1-7; \xo c \xt Deu 1:21.\x*
\p
\v 16 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ225905\add* our ancestorsВҰ225906 \add вүҲwere proud and stubborn\add* and they \add вүҲrefused to obey your instructions\add*.\x + \xo 9:16-17: \xt Num 14:1-4; Deu 1:26-33.\x*
\v 17 \add вүҲNot only did they refuseВҰ225918 to listenВҰ225919\add*, they \add вүҲforgot about all the miracles thatВҰ225924 you'd doneВҰ225925 for\add* them and they \add вүҲbecame stubborn\add* and appointedВҰ225931 a leaderВҰ225933 to take them back to their slaveryВҰ225935. \add вүҲButВҰ225918\add* you are a godВҰ225938 of forgivenessВҰ225939вҖ”graciousВҰ225940 and compassionateВҰ225941, \add вүҲslow to get angry\add* and \add вүҲgenerously showing loyal affection\add*, and you didn'tВҰ225920 abandonВҰ225951 them.\x + \xo 9:17: \xt Exo 34:6; Num 14:18.\x*
\v 18 Even when they \add вүҲmolded a metalВҰ225959\add* calf for themselves and saidВҰ225960, вҖҳThis is your godВҰ225962 who broughtВҰ225964 you \add вүҲout of\add* EgyptВҰ225965вҖҷ, and they \add вүҲbadly insulted you\add*,\x + \xo 9:18: \xt Exo 32:1-4.\x*
\v 19 you didn't abandonВҰ225974 them inВҰ225971 the wildernessВҰ225975 \add вүҲbecause you're so merciful\add*. \add вүҲYou didn't remove\add* the pillar of cloudВҰ225979 that led them onВҰ225971 the way \add вүҲduring the\add* dayВҰ225984, or \add вүЎremove\add* the pillar of fireВҰ225990 that shone atВҰ225971 nightВҰ225991 for them \add вүҲto show them\add* whichВҰ225997 way they should go.\x + \xo 9:19-21: \xt Deu 8:2-4.\x*
\v 20 You gave them your good spiritВҰ226002 to give them insight. You didn'tВҰ226007 withholdВҰ226009 your mannaВҰ226006 \add вүҲfor them to eat\add*, andВҰ226002 you \add still\add* gave them waterВҰ226011 \add вүҲto drink\add*,
\v 21 \add yes,\add* youВҰ226018 sustainedВҰ226018 them inВҰ226019 the wildernessВҰ226019 for fortyВҰ226016 yearsвҖ”they \add вүҲhad everything they needed\add*вҖ”their clothesВҰ226022 didn't wear out, andВҰ226016 their feetВҰ226025 didn't swellВҰ226027.
\p
\v 22 вҖңThenВҰ226029 you \add вүҲhanded kingdomsВҰ226031 and peopleВҰ226032 groups over to\add* them, and you \add вүҲlet them settle in even the far cornersВҰ226034 of the regionsВҰ226038\add*. They tookВҰ226035 possessionВҰ226035 of the King Sihon'sВҰ226039 HeshbonВҰ226044 \add вүҲregion\add*, and King Og'sВҰ226048 BashanВҰ226051 \add вүҲregion\add*.\x + \xo 9:22: \xt Num 21:21-35.\x*
\v 23 You \add вүҲgave our ancestors lots of childrenВҰ226053 so\add* they were like the \add many\add* starsВҰ226055 in the sky, thenВҰ226053 you broughtВҰ226057 them into this land whichВҰ226061 you'd told their ancestors to enterВҰ226065 andВҰ226053 \add вүҲtake ownership of\add*.\x + \xo 9:23: a \xt Gen 15:5; 22:17; \xo b \xt Josh 3:14-17.\x*
\v 24 Their childrenВҰ226069 went in and \add вүҲtookВҰ226070 over\add* the land \add вүҲafter you went ahead of them and\add* subduedВҰ226074 the \add previous\add* inhabitantsВҰ226078, the CanaanitesВҰ226080. You \add вүҲallowed them to defeat\add* them and their kingsВҰ226085, and the peopleВҰ226088 groups in the landвҖ”\add вүҲletting them do whatever they wanted\add* to do withВҰ226082 them.\x + \xo 9:24: \xt Josh 11:23.\x*
\v 25 They capturedВҰ226094 fortifiedВҰ226096 citiesВҰ226095 and \add вүҲproductive land\add*, and they \add вүҲtookВҰ226099 over\add* housesВҰ226100 full of all goodВҰ226105 thingsВҰ226105, \add вүҲstone\add* cisterns, vineyardsВҰ226108 and oliveВҰ226109 orchards, and \add вүҲlots of\add* fruit treesВҰ226109. They ateВҰ226113 and were satisfiedВҰ226114, and grew fat and \add вүҲenjoyed themselves as a result of yourВҰ226117 amazing\add* goodnessВҰ226117.\x + \xo 9:25: \xt Deu 6:10-11.\x*
\p
\v 26 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ226120\add* they disobeyedВҰ226120 and rebelledВҰ226121 against you, and they \add вүҲturned theirВҰ226128 backsВҰ226128 onВҰ226136 your instructions\add*. They killedВҰ226132 your prophetsВҰ226131 who testified against them inВҰ226136 orderВҰ226137 to bringВҰ226137 them back to you and they \add вүҲbadly insulted you\add*.\x + \xo 9:26-28: \xt Jdg 2:11-16.\x*
\v 27 \add вүҲSoВҰ226143\add* you \add вүҲallowed their enemies to harass and conquer\add* them. ThenВҰ226143 inВҰ226144 the timeВҰ226148 of their distressВҰ226149, they criedВҰ226150 out to you, and you yourself heardВҰ226154 from heavenВҰ226153. \add вүҲBecause you're so merciful\add*, you \add вүҲsent\add* saviours to them who rescued them from their enemies.
\v 28 After \add вүҲthey'd returned to an era of peace\add*, they reverted to doingВҰ226167 evilВҰ226168 \add вүҲagainВҰ226175 inВҰ226171 frontВҰ226169 of you\add* and you left them to \add вүҲsubmit to\add* theirВҰ226172 enemiesВҰ226172 and \add вүҲthe oppression that followed\add*. ThenВҰ226164 they'd return and cry out to you, and you heardВҰ226179 from heavenВҰ226178 and delivered them many timesВҰ226183 \add вүҲbecause you're merciful\add*.
\v 29 You \add вүҲshowed them their errors so they'd return to following your instructions, butВҰ226185 instead they ignored youВҰ226185\add* and didn'tВҰ226193 \add вүҲobey your commandsВҰ226196\add*. \add вүҲThey ignored your values whichВҰ226201 would have helped them if they'd lived\add* by them and they turnedВҰ226207 a stubbornВҰ226209 shoulderВҰ226208, stiffenedВҰ226211 their necks, and \add вүҲrefused to listen\add*.\x + \xo 9:29: \xt Lev 18:5.\x*
\v 30 \add вүҲYet\add* you \add вүҲput up\add* with them for many yearsВҰ226217, andВҰ226215 you testified against them with your spiritВҰ226221 \add вүҲthrough the messages\add* of your prophetsВҰ226224, butВҰ226215 theyВҰ226226 \add still\add* didn'tВҰ226225 \add вүҲtake any notice, so\add* you \add вүҲallowed the other peopleВҰ226229 groups to conquer\add* them.\x + \xo 9:30: \xt 2Ki 17:13-18; 2Ch 36:15-16.\x*
\v 31 \add вүҲHowever, because you're so merciful\add*, you didn't abandonВҰ226239 them and you didn't \add вүҲwipe them out completelyВҰ226237\add*. \add Yes,\add* you're a godВҰ226241 who's graciousВҰ226243 and merciful.
\p
\v 32 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ226247 now\add* God, our amazing, powerful, and awesomeВҰ226252 God who keepsВҰ226253 \add вүҲhis agreements due to his\add* loyalВҰ226255 commitment, don'tВҰ226256 \add вүҲjust ignore all our current hardshipsВҰ226263 affecting\add* us, our kings and our leadersВҰ226268, our priestsВҰ226269 and our prophetsВҰ226270, and our ancestorsВҰ226271 and all your peopleВҰ226274, from the \add вүҲperiod\add* of the Assyrian kings untilВҰ226278 today.\x + \xo 9:32: \xt 2Ki 15:19-29; 17:3-6; Ezr 4:2,10.\x*
\v 33 You are \add вүҲtotally fair in allowing all thatВҰ226287 to happen to\add* us, because youВҰ226292 have behaved faithfullyВҰ226291, butВҰ226282 \add вүҲin contrast\add*, we have behaved wickedlyВҰ226294вҖ”
\v 34 and our kingsВҰ226298, our leadersВҰ226299, our priestsВҰ226300, and our ancestorsВҰ226301 haven't \add вүҲobeyed your instructions\add* and they haven't \add вүҲbothered withВҰ226313 following\add* your commandsВҰ226309 or \add taking notice of\add* your \add вүҲcomplaints thatВҰ226311 youВҰ226312 made know to\add* them.
\v 35 \add вүҲThey servedВҰ226331 inВҰ226316 their own kingdomВҰ226316 and enjoyed the incredible goodnessВҰ226317 that you poured onВҰ226316\add* them and the wide and prosperous land that you gaveВҰ226321 them, \add вүҲbutВҰ226315\add* they didn't serveВҰ226331 you, and they didn't turn away from their evilВҰ226336 actions.
\p
\v 36 вҖң\add вүҲTake notice of\add* us todayвҖ”we're servants, and the land thatВҰ226343 you gaveВҰ226345 to our ancestorsВҰ226346 \add вүҲso we could\add* eatВҰ226347 its fruitВҰ226350 and its produceВҰ226350, \add вүҲbutВҰ226342 look at us now\add*вҖ”we're servants in \add @our own land\add*.
\v 37 \add вүҲNow\add* itsВҰ226359 plentiful produceВҰ226359 belongs to the kingsВҰ226361 who \add вүҲyou'veВҰ226364 placed over us due to\add* our sinsВҰ226366, and who rule over our bodiesВҰ226368 and over our livestockВҰ226370 \add вүҲjust however theyВҰ226369 want to, so\add* we're \add вүҲterribly distressedВҰ226372\add*.
\rem /s1 Those Who Signed the Covenant; The People Sign an Agreement; The Agreement of the People
\p
\v 38 вҖң\add вүҲSo now\add* in all of this, we're \add вүҲfaithfully making an agreement\add*, and our leaders, our Levites, and our priests will even write it down on a document \add вүҲand sign it\add*.вҖқ
