\v 28 The rest of the people, the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the \add вүҲsingers\add*, the gatekeepers, and all the \add вүҲpeople who were prepared to dedicate themselves to obeying God rather than the customs of the former inhabitants of the land\add*, their wives, their sons and their daughters, \add and\add* \add вүҲeveryone who was old enough to understand\add*,
\v 29 were \add вүҲjoining with\add* their brothers, their nobles, and were \add вүҲcommitting to a promise which also had\add* a curse: to \add вүҲobey God's instructions as\add* given by God's servantВҰ226557 Mosheh, and to keep and to do all the commands of Yahweh our master, \add вүҲaccepting\add* his judgements and his statutes.
