\p
\v 32 We \add вүҲwill also pledge to each donate a week's wages each yearВҰ226643 to support the temple functions\add*\x + \xo 10:32: \xt Exo 30:11-16.\x*
\v 33 \add includingВҰ226651\add* the bread \add displayed\add* inВҰ226658 rows, the continual offering and the continual burnt offering, for the rest day \add offerings\add* and the new moons, for the appointed times and for the holy things, for the sin offerings to cover over Yisrael's \add guilt\add*, and for all the \add вүҲoperation\add* of God's residence.
\p
\v 34 Then we \add вүҲthrew dice\add* \add to choose from\add* among the priests, the Levites, and the people \add вүҲto create the roster for\add* bringing \add вүҲfirewood to the temple as an\add* offeringВҰ226674 \add вүҲto be used\add* at the appointedВҰ226672 times \add вүҲeach\add* year for burning on the altar of Yahweh ourВҰ226683 godВҰ226683 as written in the \add вүҲscrolls\add*.
\p
\v 35 Every year \add we will also\add* bringВҰ226696 the \add вүҲearly produce from\add* our soil and the \add вүҲfirst harvest from\add* every fruit tree to Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*.\x + \xo 10:35: \xt Exo 23:19; 34:26; Deu 26:2.\x*
