\rem /s1 Dedication of the City Wall; Nehemiah Dedicates the City Wall; Dedication of Jerusalem's Wall; Dedication of the Wall of Jerusalem
\p
\v 27 At the dedication of the wallВҰ227584 \add вүҲaround\add* Yerushalem, they \add вүҲsummoned\add* LevitesВҰ227589 from all \add вүҲover the region\add* to come to Yerushalem to perform the dedication with rejoicing and thanksgivingВҰ227598, and with \add вүҲmusical instruments and singingВҰ227599\add*,
\v 28 \add вүҲplusВҰ227607 the next generation\add* of singersВҰ227606 came both from YerushalemВҰ227611 and its surrounds, and from the NetofatiВҰ227615 villagesВҰ227614.
\v 29 \add They also\add* \add вүЎcame\add* from Beyt-Gilgal, and from the fieldsВҰ227619 of Geva and AzmavetВҰ227621, because the singersВҰ227626 had builtВҰ227624 villagesВҰ227623 near YerushalemВҰ227628 to live in.
\v 30 The priestsВҰ227631 and LevitesВҰ227632 \add вүҲheld a purification ceremony for\add* themselvesВҰ227630, thenВҰ227630 they purified the peopleВҰ227636 and the gatesВҰ227639 and the wallВҰ227642.
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ227644 I \add вүҲassembled\add* Yehudah'sВҰ227648 leadersВҰ227647 together up on top of the wall, andВҰ227644 I \add вүҲassigned\add* them into twoВҰ227652 largeВҰ227654 groups \add вүҲwho would give thanksВҰ227653\add* \add as they walked around it\add*.
\p \add вүҲThe first group\add* headed towards the Dung Gate on the rightВҰ227656.
\v 32 HoshayahВҰ227664 andВҰ227665 half of Yehudah'sВҰ227667 officials \add вүҲwere in that group\add*
\v 33 \add вүҲalong with\add* Azaryah, EzraВҰ227670, andВҰ227671 MeshullamВҰ227671,
\v 34 Yehudah, BenyaminВҰ227674, ShemayahВҰ227675, and Yirmeyah,
\v 35 plusВҰ227679 some of the \add вүҲnext generation\add* of priestsВҰ227680 withВҰ227681 trumpetsВҰ227681: Zekaryah (son of Yonatan, son of ShemayahВҰ227688, son of MattanyahВҰ227691, son of Mikayah, son of Zakkur, son of AsafВҰ227700)
\v 36 and his brothersВҰ227702 ShemayahВҰ227703, Azar'el, MilalaiВҰ227705, GilalaiВҰ227706, Ma'ai, Nethan'el, Yehudah, \add and\add* HananiВҰ227710. \add They used\add* the instruments \add вүҲas per the instructions\add* of \add the late King\add* DavidВҰ227714, the manВҰ227715 of God. EzraВҰ227717 the scribeВҰ227718 \add вүҲwent inВҰ227711 frontВҰ227719 of them\add*.
\v 37 WhenВҰ227721 they got to the Fountain Gate, they wentВҰ227725 up the stairs atВҰ227731 the City of David, \add вүҲandВҰ227721 along the higher portion of the wallВҰ227732 by David'sВҰ227730 palace\add* as far as the Water Gate (\add вүҲonВҰ227731 the east\add* \add side of the cityВҰ227729\add*).
\p
\v 38 The \add вүҲother group giving thanksВҰ227741\add* with the other half of the peopleВҰ227748 wentВҰ227743 in the opposite direction \add around the top of the wall\add*вҖ”goingВҰ227743 past the Tower of the Ovens to the \add вүҲwider part\add* of the wall.
\v 39 \add We passed\add* EfrayimВҰ227761 Gate, the Old Gate, Fish Gate, and HananelВҰ227771 Tower, the Tower of the HundredВҰ227773, \add вүҲand all the way to\add* the Sheep Gate, and we \add вүҲstoppedВҰ227779 atВҰ227780\add* the Guard Gate.
\p
\v 40 ThenВҰ227783 \add вүҲbothВҰ227784\add* groups \add вүҲended up at the temple\add* andВҰ227783 stoodВҰ227783 there. I was there with the half of the city officialsВҰ227790 who'd \add accompanied\add* me,
\v 41 \add вүҲas well as\add* the priestsВҰ227793 withВҰ227801 their trumpetsВҰ227801: Elyakim, Ma'aseyah, Minyamin, Mikayah, Elyeoenai, Zekaryah, Hanayah,
\v 42 \add another\add* Ma'aseyah, ShemayahВҰ227804, El'azar, UzziВҰ227806, YehohananВҰ227807, Malkiyyah, Eylam, andВҰ227803 EzerВҰ227810. The singersВҰ227812 sang loudly with their leaderВҰ227814 YizrahyahВҰ227813.
\p
\v 43 ThenВҰ227816 that \add same\add* dayВҰ227817 they offeredВҰ227816 many sacrificesВҰ227820, and they \add вүҲcelebrated\add* because God had made them very pleased. The womenВҰ227829 and children also celebrated, \add in fact\add* the sound of the celebrations in YerushalemВҰ227834 was so loud that itВҰ227832 can be heardВҰ227832 far away.
\s1 Supporting the temple operation
\rem /s1 Provisions for Temple Worship; Temple Responsibilities; Providing for Worship in the Temple
\p
\v 44 ThenВҰ227837 \add still onВҰ227838\add* that \add same\add* dayВҰ227838, menВҰ227840 were appointedВҰ227837 \add вүҲto be inВҰ227838 charge of the storeroomsВҰ227844\add* for the tithesВҰ227847 and offerings. The \add вүҲpercentages\add* for the priests and the Levites were gatheredВҰ227848 from the fieldsВҰ227850 around the citiesВҰ227851 as per the \add written\add* law, because \add the people of\add* YehudahВҰ227858 \add вүҲwere happy to have\add* the priests and the Levites \add вүҲserving\add*.
\v 45 They \add вүҲserved GodВҰ227869 with theirВҰ227869 daily duties and the purificationВҰ227871 ceremonies\add*, as well as \add the duties of\add* the singersВҰ227874 and gatekeepersВҰ227875вҖ”\add вүҲall done accordingВҰ227876 to the instructions\add* \add left by King\add* DavidВҰ227877 and his son Shelomoh,\x + \xo 12:45: a \xt 1Ch 25:1-8; \xo b \xt 1Ch 26:12.\x*
\v 46 because it was \add handed down\add* from the original singersВҰ227889 who sang songsВҰ227890 of praiseВҰ227892 and thanksgivingВҰ227893 to GodВҰ227894 inВҰ227883 the timeВҰ227883 of DavidВҰ227884 and AsafВҰ227885.
\v 47 In Zerubavel and Nehemyah'sВҰ227902 times, all YisraelВҰ227898 \add вүҲcontributed the daily food allowance\add* for the singersВҰ227905 and gatekeepersВҰ227906. They \add вүҲalso gave a percentage\add* to the LevitesВҰ227912 \add вүҲwho thenВҰ227896 gave a percentage of that\add* to \add the priests\add* (Aharon's descendantsВҰ227915).
\c 13
\s1 Separating out the foreigners
\rem /s1 Nehemiah's religious reforms; Nehemiah's Final Reforms; Separation from Foreigners; Foreigners Separated from Israel; Nehemiah's Various Reforms
\p
\v 1 That dayВҰ227919, the \add вүҲMoshehВҰ227923 scrollВҰ227922 was read out aloudВҰ227921 to\add* the peopleВҰ227925, and it was \add вүҲdiscovered that it had been writtenВҰ227927 that no AmmoniteВҰ227933 or Moabite is ever allowed to join the congregation\add*\x + \xo 13:1-2: \xt Deu 23:3-5.\x*
\v 2 because \add вүҲinstead of helping the travelling IsraelisВҰ227946 withВҰ227948 food\add* and waterВҰ227949, theyВҰ227943 had hiredВҰ227950 Bil'amВҰ227947 \add (BalaamВҰ227954)\add* to curse them (even though GodВҰ227957 had turnedВҰ227956 that curse into blessingВҰ227959).\x + \xo 13:2: \xt Num 22:1-6.\x*
\v 3 \add вүҲAfterВҰ227970\add* hearing \add *that\add*, theyВҰ227962 separatedВҰ227966 out all of \add вүҲthe foreigners\add*.
\s1 Nehemyah's reforms
\rem /s1 Nehemiah's Reforms; The Reforms of Nehemiah
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲPrior to that time,\add* the high priestВҰ227975 Elyashiv (closely related to Toviyyah) had been inВҰ227977 charge of the \add вүҲtemple storeroomsВҰ227977\add*
\v 5 and he'd \add вүҲallowed\add* \add ?@Toviyyah\add* to have a largeВҰ227987 room that had previously been used to store offerings: the frankincenseВҰ227995, the utensilsВҰ227996, and \add вүҲdonated\add* grain, wine, and oil, (the percentage commandedВҰ228001 \add to be given to\add* the LevitesВҰ228002, the singersВҰ228003, and the gatekeepersВҰ228004), and the offerings for the priestsВҰ228006.
\v 6 \add вүҲDuring all that period,\add* I hadn't been in YerushalemВҰ228013 because I'd returned to the Babylonian king in the 32nd year of Artahshashta's reign \add (ArtaxerxesВҰ228018)\add*. \add вүҲHowever, after a while\add* I requestedВҰ228028 leaveВҰ228028 \add again\add* from the king
\v 7 andВҰ228035 I cameВҰ228033 \add back\add* to YerushalemВҰ228034. \add It was thenВҰ228033 thatВҰ228037\add* \add вүҲI discoveredВҰ228035 how\add* evilВҰ228036 Elyashiv had been by making a storeroom for Toviyyah inВҰ228036 the courtsВҰ228044 of God's residence.
\v 8 \add вүҲIt made me very upset\add* andВҰ228051 I threwВҰ228051 everything of Toviyyah's out of the roomВҰ228063.
\v 9 ThenВҰ228065 I \add вүҲorderedВҰ228065 the storeroomsВҰ228067 to be purifiedВҰ228066\add* \add by the priests\add* \add вүҲbefore\add* I returnedВҰ228068 the \add вүҲtemple utensilsВҰ228070\add* to the room, along with the grainВҰ228075 offeringsВҰ228075 andВҰ228065 the incense.
\p
\v 10 IВҰ228090 \add вүҲfoundВҰ228079 out\add* that the LevitesВҰ228083 and the singersВҰ228091 weren't being givenВҰ228085 their percentageВҰ228079, \add so they'd left their duties and\add* returned to \add cultivate\add* their own fieldsВҰ228089.\x + \xo 13:10: \xt Deu 12:19.\x*
\v 11 I \add вүҲmade a complaint to\add* the officialsВҰ228098 asking why the \add вүҲoperation of the temple had been neglectedВҰ228101\add*, and thenВҰ228095 I \add вүҲrounded up\add* \add @the Levites and the singers\add* and \add вүҲsent them back to theirВҰ228110 duties\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲAfter that,\add* \add the people of\add* YehudahВҰ228114 \add вүҲstarted bringing\add* a tenth of \add &their\add* grainВҰ228117 and wine and oilВҰ228119 to the storeroomsВҰ228120.\x + \xo 13:12: \xt Mal 3:10.\x*
\v 13 I appointedВҰ228122 \add вүҲbook-keepers\add* over the storeroomsВҰ228125: the priestВҰ228127 ShelemyahВҰ228126, the scribeВҰ228129 TsadokВҰ228128, and the LeviteВҰ228133 PedayahВҰ228130 with HananВҰ228137 (the son of Zakkur, the son of MattanyahВҰ228143) \add вүҲhelping\add*. They were \add all\add* considered trustworthy, and \add вүҲtheir job included distributingВҰ228148 the produce among their colleagues\add*.
\mi
\v 14 MyВҰ228155 godВҰ228155, rememberВҰ228152 me \add вүҲhandling all these issues\add* and don'tВҰ228159 wipe out my loyalВҰ228162 kindness for \add вүҲyour temple and itsВҰ228167 operation\add* \add thatВҰ228163 I'veВҰ228164 shown\add*.
\s1 The rest day
\rem /s1 Sabbath Reforms Begun
\p
\v 15 In thoseВҰ228170 daysВҰ228169 I saw \add people\add* in YehudahВҰ228172 \add working\add* on the rest dayвҖ”treading wine, bringing in grainВҰ228181, and loadingВҰ228182 donkeysВҰ228185, yes, even bringing wine, grapesВҰ228189, figs, and all kinds of loads into YerushalemВҰ228195 on the rest day. I \add вүҲcomplained to them when they were sellingВҰ228200 the goods\add*.\x + \xo 13:15: \xt Exo 20:8-10; Deu 5:12-14; Jer 17:21-22.\x*
\v 16 \add вүҲAlso, peopleВҰ228213 from Tsor\add* \add (Tyre)\add* were bringingВҰ228206 in fishВҰ228207 and all kinds of merchandiseВҰ228210 and were sellingВҰ228211 it onВҰ228205 the rest day to the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*, even in YerushalemВҰ228215.
\v 17 IВҰ228220 rebukedВҰ228217 the Yehudah \add вүҲbusiness leaders\add*, asking them, вҖңWhat's this evil thingВҰ228225 thatВҰ228228 you're all doingВҰ228230вҖ”profaningВҰ228231 the rest day \add by treating it like a regular day\add*?
\v 18 \add вүҲWasn't that what yourВҰ228240 ancestorsВҰ228240 didВҰ228239вҖ”the very reason\add* ourВҰ228242 godВҰ228242 broughtВҰ228241 all this evil on us and on this cityВҰ228250? \add вүҲNow\add* you're all \add вүҲmaking GodВҰ228242 angry with\add* YisraelВҰ228257 \add again\add* by profaningВҰ228258 the rest day.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲSo after that, when it started to get dark on Friday evenings, I orderedВҰ228274 that the city gates be closedВҰ228272, and not to be openedВҰ228277 untilВҰ228278 after the rest day\add*. I \add вүҲalso stationedВҰ228282 some of my young men to stand at the gates to ensure that no load could enter on the rest day\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲSomeВҰ228300 tradersВҰ228294 andВҰ228293 merchantsВҰ228294 selling various goods camped outsideВҰ228299 the city walls once or twiceВҰ228302\add*,
\v 21 \add вүҲbutВҰ228304 I warnedВҰ228304\add* them, вҖңWhy are you \add вүҲcamping there outside\add* the wallВҰ228312? If you \add вүҲdoВҰ228315 it againВҰ228315, I'llВҰ228317 have you all removed\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲAfter that\add*, theyВҰ228325 \add вүҲno longer cameВҰ228325 onВҰ228318 the rest days\add*.
\v 22 Then I told the LevitesВҰ228330 that theyВҰ228332 should purifyВҰ228333 themselvesВҰ228333 and then comeВҰ228334 to the gatesВҰ228336 to \add вүҲmonitor them on the rest dayВҰ228340\add*.
\mi My godВҰ228348, rememberВҰ228345 me \add вүҲhaving to deal with this, and show yourВҰ228352 amazing loyalВҰ228352 faithfulness towards me\add*.
\s1 The scolding of marriage of foreigner
\rem /s1 Mixed Marriages Condemned
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲDuring that timeВҰ228357\add*, I also sawВҰ228359 Jews who'd \add вүҲmarriedВҰ228363\add* womenВҰ228364 \add вүҲfrom AshdodВҰ228365, Ammon, and Moav\add*,
\v 24 and half of theirВҰ228373 childrenВҰ228373 spoke \add вүҲa foreign languageВҰ228381 from those other people groups\add* and \add вүҲcouldn't speakВҰ228375 Hebrew\add*.
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ228385\add* I scolded \add @those men\add* and cursedВҰ228387 them and hit \add some of\add* them and pulledВҰ228391 out their hair. ThenВҰ228385 I \add вүҲforced them to promise inВҰ228393 front onВҰ228393 GodВҰ228393 that they wouldn't allow their daughters to marry foreign men, or their sons to take foreign wives\add*.
\v 26 \add I explained,\add* вҖңDidn't Yisrael'sВҰ228414 \add own\add* KingВҰ228413 Shelomoh sin concerning that same matter? Among \add вүҲall the countriesВҰ228415\add* \add inВҰ228415 the world\add*, there wasn't any other king like, and he was lovedВҰ228422 by his godВҰ228423 who'd placed him \add there\add* as king over all Yisrael. \add ButВҰ228415 even then,\add* the foreignВҰ228438 womenВҰ228437 causedВҰ228436 him to sin.
\v 27 \add вүҲSoВҰ228440 doВҰ228442 weВҰ228441 need to\add* hearВҰ228441 about all of youВҰ228440 doing this terrible evilВҰ228446 of being unfaithfulВҰ228449 to GodВҰ228450 by marryingВҰ228451 foreignВҰ228453 wivesВҰ228452?вҖқ
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲAlso\add* one of Yoyada's sonsВҰ228455 (grandson of the highВҰ228461 priestВҰ228460 Elyashiv) was a son-in-law of Sanvallat the HoroniteВҰ228464, \add вүҲso I banished himВҰ228465 from my sight\add*.\x + \xo 13:28: \xt Neh 4:1.\x*
\mi
\v 29 MyВҰ228470 godВҰ228470, remember them for \add вүҲbringing shame to\add* the priesthood and \add вүҲdishonouring the vows made by\add* the \add вүҲpriests\add* and the LevitesВҰ228476.
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ228478 IВҰ228482 purifiedВҰ228478 them from everything foreignВҰ228481, \add вүҲestablishedВҰ228482 regulations for each part of the workВҰ228487 done by\add* the priestsВҰ228484 andВҰ228478 the LevitesВҰ228485,
\v 31 andВҰ228493 \add вүҲorganised the firewood supply atВҰ228491 certain\add* timesВҰ228491, \add вүҲincludingВҰ228493\add* for the first-fruits \add celebrations\add*.
\mi MyВҰ228498 godВҰ228498, rememberВҰ228495 me for goodВҰ228499.
